{"person": "MALLET PARET, LOUIS", "education": "Educated at Stonyhurst College, Lancashire", "birth_year": null, "events": [{"position": "acting commissioner of the tribunal of appeal", "place": "St. Lucia", "year_start": 1868, "year_end": 1868, "is_acting": true, "org_type": "civil"}, {"position": "administrator-general of crown property", "place": "St. Lucia", "year_start": 1868, "year_end": 1868, "is_acting": true, "org_type": "civil"}, {"position": "commissioner of the tribunal of appeal", "place": "St. Lucia", "year_start": 1869, "year_end": 1869, "is_acting": false, "org_type": "civil"}, {"position": "administrator-general of crown property", "place": "St. Lucia", "year_start": 1869, "year_end": 1869, "is_acting": false, "org_type": "civil"}, {"position": "member of the board of education", "place": "St. Lucia", "year_start": 1869, "year_end": 1869, "is_acting": false, "org_type": "civil"}, {"position": "inspector of Catholic schools", "place": "St. Lucia", "year_start": 1869, "year_end": 1869, "is_acting": false, "org_type": "civil"}, {"position": "colonial trustee", "place": "St. Lucia", "year_start": 1871, "year_end": 1871, "is_acting": false, "org_type": "civil"}, {"position": "stipendiary magistrate of the Hirst district", "place": "St. Lucia", "year_start": 1873, "year_end": 1873, "is_acting": false, "org_type": "civil"}, {"position": "deputy coroner for the first district", "place": "St. Lucia", "year_start": 1876, "year_end": 1876, "is_acting": false, "org_type": "civil"}, {"position": "acting colonial treasurer", "place": "St. Lucia", "year_start": 1876, "year_end": 1876, "is_acting": true, "org_type": "civil"}], "terminal": null, "honours": [], "notes": "Admitted to practice as an advocate at the St. Lucia bar, 1865; called to the bar, Middle Temple, 1868; joined the service in 1868, as acting commissioner of the tribunal of appeal, and administrator-general of crown property; confirmed in these appointments in June, 1869. A member of the board of education and an inspector of Catholic schools, 1869; appointed colonial trustee, 1871, on the abolition of the office of commissioner of appeals, when the duties of administrator were transferred to the new office; acted as stipendiary magistrate of the Hirst district in 1873; commissioned a deputy coroner for the first district in 1876; appointed on two occasions to inquire into matters connected with the public institutions of the colony, and received the thanks of the government; acting colonial treasurer, December, 1876; ex officio a member of legislative and executive councils.", "person_id": "kgp_col1878-p411b4"}
